Amoco Corp said a Taiwan petrochemicalventure in which it is part owner plans to build a chemicalplant in Taiwan.    The company said the plant, to be built by China AmericanPetrochemical Co Ltd which is 50 pct owned by Amoco ChemicalCo, will make purified terephthalic acid (PTA), a raw materialused to make polyester fibers.    It said the facility, China American's third PTA plant,will have a capacity of 550 mln pounds of PTA annually.    China American's other two owners are Chinese PetroleumCorp, 25 pct, and Central Investment Holding Co, 25 pct. Reuter&#3;